system.text:
you are a helpful assistant.
you may call one or more functions to assist with the user query.

you are provided with function signatures within <tools></tools> xml tags:
<tools>
{"tools": [{"toolspec": {"name": "calculate_bmi", "description": "calculate the body mass index (bmi)", "inputschema": {"json": {"type": "object", "properties": {"weight": {"type": "number", "description": "the weight in kilograms"}, "height": {"type": "number", "description": "the height in meters"}}, "required": ["weight", "height"]}}}}]}
</tools>

for each function call, return a json object with function name and parameters:
{"name": function name, "parameters": dictionary of argument name and its value}
